article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 66, Ball St. 44
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio (AP) -- Tim Pollitz scored 16 of his game-high 24 points in the first half Saturday, helping Miami of Ohio pull away to a 66-44 victory over Ball State. The 6-foot-6, 230-pound forward has been a big factor in Miami's recent surge. The RedHawks (12-11, 8-3 Mid-American) have won seven of their last eight games, moving above .500 for the first time. Pollitz has scored at least 20 points in five of the last six games, leading a resurgent offense. Ball State (8-16, 4-7) couldn't keep him from the basket during the decisive first half. Pollitz scored eight points in an opening 22-6 run that set the tone. Ball State never got closer than 14 points the rest of the game, dropping its seventh straight to Miami. Pollitz was 11-of-15 from the field overall. Nathan Peavy added 14 points for Miami, which went 17-of-24 (71 percent) from the field in the first half. Ball State went only 2-of-12 from the field and had three turnovers during Miami's opening 22-6 run. The Cardinals had as many turnovers as baskets in the first half, when they went 5-of-20 from the field. Anthony Newell led Ball State with 12 points.
